1
00:00:00,140 --> 00:00:02,560
We are Christians, Armenian Orthodox

2
00:00:04,007 --> 00:00:06,470
We are committed to this legacy

3
00:00:09,683 --> 00:00:12,470
The Armenian community comes to this church

4
00:00:13,404 --> 00:00:14,654
It was thriving

5
00:00:15,295 --> 00:00:17,551
It had pews, 40 seats

6
00:00:18,685 --> 00:00:20,464
And the communion bread was there

7
00:00:21,278 --> 00:00:23,711
Here is the sanctuary, this is what you see in front of you now

8
00:00:26,245 --> 00:00:28,303
Now there is no one

9
00:00:30,836 --> 00:00:36,292
Interviewer: What are the main differences between the Christian denominations?

10
00:00:36,478 --> 00:00:37,479
What do you mean?

11
00:00:37,532 --> 00:00:39,953
Interviewer: Like between Chaldean, Syriac, or Armenian?

12
00:00:40,125 --> 00:00:41,586
We are different from them

13
00:00:42,897 --> 00:00:45,377
The church is like other churches

14
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:48,556
But in the name and the rite there is a difference

15
00:00:49,195 --> 00:00:51,886
For example, we are Armenian Orthodox

16
00:00:52,821 --> 00:00:56,102
And behind us are Syriac Orthodox

17
00:00:56,908 --> 00:00:58,108
And Syriac Catholics

18
00:01:00,510 --> 00:01:02,603
And the Pope’s group is also present in the square

19
00:01:02,670 --> 00:01:03,855
That is the difference

20
00:01:03,975 --> 00:01:08,175
As for religion and politics, there is no difference

21
00:01:09,403 --> 00:01:12,905
We only pray and worship

22
00:01:14,770 --> 00:01:16,003
That is the difference between us

23
00:01:16,894 --> 00:01:17,894
Between the churches

24
00:01:19,360 --> 00:01:24,291
In 1924 we were displaced

25
00:01:25,254 --> 00:01:29,790
It was Patrick’s grandfather—Dr. Patrick, his grandfather

26
00:01:30,082 --> 00:01:31,395
He received them here

27
00:01:32,128 --> 00:01:35,816
He sheltered them, and gave them clothing, food, and drink

28
00:01:36,363 --> 00:01:38,910
For four years or five years

29
00:01:39,731 --> 00:01:42,351
And we were obliged to build this church here

30
00:01:47,191 --> 00:01:51,424
Interviewer: Who were the prominent figures?

31
00:01:51,465 --> 00:01:52,824
The prominent figures…

32
00:01:53,451 --> 00:01:55,589
Dr. Patrick Jakhmashian

33
00:01:56,599 --> 00:01:58,993
Joseph Jakhmashian

34
00:02:01,434 --> 00:02:03,044
Artin Arzevian

35
00:02:04,545 --> 00:02:08,360
Mukhtar Khachik lived here, opposite the church

36
00:02:09,060 --> 00:02:10,361
Those were the ones

37
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:12,649
I do not remember the other names

38
00:02:13,664 --> 00:02:14,790
Interviewer: What is the most notable thing

39
00:02:15,377 --> 00:02:18,832
That those figures you mentioned did for this place?

40
00:02:18,914 --> 00:02:20,885
They are the ones who built the church

41
00:02:21,213 --> 00:02:24,418
And they ran the church’s work, they did everything

42
00:02:25,424 --> 00:02:27,297
Administratively or economically
